<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900611-0057</DOCNO><DOCID>900611-0057.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Texas Instruments Inc.:   Jobs for Defense to Be Cut   By 1,000 Over 12 Months</HL><DATE>06/11/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   TXN PHG</CO><LP>   Texas Instruments Inc. said it will reduce its defensesystems work force by about 1,000 employees over the nextyear in response to reduced defense spending.   The Dallas-based semiconductor and defense concern saidthat all its Defense Systems and Electronics Group sites,which employ about 22,000 people, will be affected by thedecision.</LP><TEXT>   Texas Instruments said it expects the overall financialimpact from the reductions to be minimal.   The company also announced it agreed with a unit of theNetherlands' N.V. Philips to swap designs for a group ofcomputer chips called bus-interface logics.   Under the agreement, Texas Instruments and PhilipsComponents-Signetics will make and sell each other'sbus-interface chips, which act as go-betweens in computers,allowing chips to communicate with each other and to outsideequipment such as telephone lines.   Texas Instruments estimates the world market forbus-interface chips at about $850 million.</TEXT></DOC>